# Project Structure & Navigation

This project is an investment note and analysis system. Main directory structure:

```
InvestNote-py/
├── main.py               # FastAPI entry, starts API service
├── invest_note.py        # Legacy CLI/interactive entry
├── requirements.txt      # Dependencies
├── core/                 # Core modules
│   ├── handler/          # Data orchestration (DataSourceHelper, K-line, strategy, etc.)
│   ├── analysis/         # Backtesting, strategy evaluation, visualization
│   ├── strategy/         # Strategy implementations
│   ├── indicator/        # Technical indicators
│   ├── score/            # Scoring system
│   ├── filter/           # Stock filters
│   ├── valuation/        # Valuation
│   ├── enum/             # Enums
│   ├── models/           # Data models
│   ├── service/          # DB and repository services
│   ├── database/         # DB adapters/tools
│   └── utils/            # Utilities and helpers
├── api/                  # FastAPI route definitions and API models
├── output/               # Output (json, reports, etc.)
├── tools/                # Helper scripts/tools
├── sql/                  # SQL scripts
├── web/                  # (Optional) Web-related FastAPI routes/interfaces
├── README.md             # Project documentation
├── config/               # Configuration files (e.g., cron.yaml)
```

## Entry Points
- Recommended: [main.py](mdc:main.py) for FastAPI service, routes in [api.py](mdc:api.py).
- Legacy CLI: [invest_note.py](mdc:invest_note.py) for batch/interactive analysis.

## Core Data Flow
- Data orchestration and processing are mainly via [data_source_helper.py](mdc:core/data_source_helper.py)'s `DataSourceHelper`.
- Strategy, indicator, scoring, filtering, etc. are in separate subdirectories for easy extension.

## Dependencies & Environment
- See [requirements.txt](mdc:requirements.txt) for dependencies.
- Configuration files (e.g., cron jobs) are in [config/](mdc:config).
